article.headline: Boston College 77, Alabama 56
article.story:
FORT COLLINS, Colo. (AP) -- Jessalyn Deveny had 23 points and
seven rebounds and Amber Jacobs added 20 points as Boston College
routed Alabama 77-56 in the Rocky Mountain Invitational on Friday
night.

Deveny was 9-for-11 shooting and Jacobs was 7-for-9 for Boston
College (3-0). The Eagles shot 56 percent from the field overall
and 71 percent in the second half.

Tamisha Hamilton had 13 points to lead Alabama (1-1). The
Crimson Tide had 22 turnovers.

Deveny hit her first three shots of the second half, one a
3-pointer, to extend Boston College's lead to 51-34. The Eagles led
61-40 with 8:10 left after baskets by Brooke Queenan and Sarah
Marshall.

Alabama, which was 9-for-33 shooting in the second half, never
got closer than 17 points the rest of the way.

The Boston College backcourt of Deveny and Jacobs combined for
27 points in the first half to build a 39-30 lead. Alabama shot 52
percent in the half and was as close as 29-28, but Boston College
had a 10-2 run before halftime, including a 3-pointer by Clare
Droesch.
